eligibilityCriteria.text:
Hepatic dysfunction defined as:
 Total bilirubin  1.5 × ULN unless the participant has documented Gilbert's syndrome (in this case total bilirubin ≥3 × ULN);

 AST and ALT  3 × ULN;  5.0 × ULN if there is liver involvement by the tumor;

 Alkaline phosphatase  2.5 × ULN (unless the participant has bone metastasis only, in which case the alkaline phosphatase value will not be considered as exclusion criteria).

 aPTT  1.25 × ULN and INR  1.25 unless the participant is receiving anticoagulation, then aPTT and INR should be within the therapeutic range of the intended use.

13. Hematologic abnormalities defined as:

 ANC  1,500/mm 3 or 1.5 × 10 9 /L;

 Platelets  100,000/mm 3 or 100 × 10 9 /L;

 Hemoglobin  9 g/dL. One transfusion allowed ≤2 weeks before study enrollment.
